  "architectureSummary": "This project implements a Spring Boot microservice for managing bank accounts. It follows a layered architecture, typical for Spring applications, separating concerns into distinct components. The application exposes RESTful APIs for CRUD operations on customer and account details, integrates with a database using Spring Data JPA, and includes robust error handling and API documentation.\n\n## Layers\n*   **Application Layer**: The entry point and orchestrator of the Spring Boot application (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/AccountsApplication.java`).\n*   **Controller Layer**: Handles incoming HTTP requests, performs input validation, and delegates business logic to the service layer (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/controller/AccountsController.java`).\n*   **Service Layer**: Contains the core business logic and transaction management. It defines an interface (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/service/IAccountService.java`) and an implementation (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/service/impl/AccountService.java`).\n*   **Repository Layer**: Manages data persistence operations using Spring Data JPA, interacting with the underlying database (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/repository/AccountsRepository.java`, `src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/repository/CustomerRepository.java`).\n*   **Entity Layer**: Defines the domain model objects that map to database tables (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/entity/Accounts.java`, `src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/entity/Customer.java`, `src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/entity/BaseEntity.java`).\n*   **DTO Layer**: Data Transfer Objects used for request and response payloads, often including validation annotations (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/dto/*.java`).\n*   **Mapper Layer**: Utility classes responsible for converting between DTOs and Entities (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/mapper/AccountsMapper.java`, `src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/mapper/CustomerMapper.java`).\n*   **Exception Handling Layer**: Custom exceptions (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/exception/CustomerAlreadyExistsException.java`, `src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/exception/ResourceNotFoundException.java`) and a global handler (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/exception/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`) for consistent error responses.\n*   **Audit Layer**: Provides auditing capabilities for entities (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/audit/AuditAwareImpl.java`).\n*   **Constants Layer**: Holds application-wide constant values (`src/main/java/com/bank/accounts/constants/AccountsConstants.java`).\n\n## Data Flow\nClient requests hit the `AccountsController`, which validates input (using DTOs) and calls the `IAccountService`. The `AccountService` orchestrates business logic, interacting with `AccountsRepository` and `CustomerRepository` for data access. Mappers convert entities to DTOs for responses. Exceptions are caught and processed by `GlobalExceptionHandler` to return standardized error messages.\n\n## Key Observations\n*   The use of Lombok reduces boilerplate code for DTOs and Entities.\n*   Spring Data JPA simplifies database interactions.\n*   Swagger/OpenAPI annotations provide clear API documentation.\n*   Centralized exception handling ensures consistent error responses.\n*   The `application.yml` configures the H2 in-memory database for development/testing and imports configuration from a config server, indicating a microservice pattern for externalized configuration.",
